1. UK pregnant women had whole-blood Se concentration lower than the mid-range of other populations.
2. UK pregnant women had toenail Se concentration considerably lower than US women.
3. UK pregnant women had GPx3 activity considerably lower than US and Australian pregnant women.
4. UK pregnant women had low baseline SEPP1 concentration.
5. The median SEPP1 concentration in UK pregnant women was 3.00 mg/l.
6. The range of SEPP1 concentration in UK pregnant women was 0.90–5.80 mg/l.
